Input - (session id, project_id, file)

This parses the give code file and creates a concrete syntax tree using library like tree-sitter
Then it navigates through each component

1. If it is a comment block, apply the commmentOut strategy in the compressor module
The comment blocks are usually present just above the class definitions, method definitions or variables.
In the majority of the situations, there will not be useful information present in the comment blocks, 
since the current day models are smart enough to understand the context directly from the actual code blocks.

2. If it is a class/method/variable, apply the compactBlock strategy in the compressor module
We can squash the code in a much compacter way than what we have already written in.
The key insight is that models don't need full identifiers to reason — they need structure and relationships. 
A function like:
// Before
void processCustomerOrderWithValidation(Order& order, Customer& customer) {
    validateOrderItems(order);
    applyCustomerDiscounts(customer, order);
    ...
}
//After
void f1(O& o, C& c) { f2(o); f3(c,o); ... }

Ouput - (session_id, project_id, compressed file)